All done. Here's a summary of what was completed:

## Completed: Migrate from JSON File Storage to SQLite

**Branch:** `feature/Migrate-from-JSON-File-Storage-to-SQLite`
**Card:** Moved to "Ready to Review"

### Changes Made

1. **New `services/db.js`** — SQLite database layer using `better-sqlite3`
   - 9 tables: `brands`, `listings`, `reports`, `users`, `sessions`, `seller_history`, `image_hashes`, `skus`, `serp_reports`
   - Proper indexes on `brandId`, `status`, `itemId`, `email`, etc.
   - WAL mode for concurrent read performance
   - JSON column serialize/deserialize helpers
   - One-time auto-migration from existing JSON files on first startup

2. **Rewritten services:**
   - `services/monitor.js` — brands, listings, reports, seller history all use SQLite. New `insertListings()` for efficient batch inserts during scans
   - `services/users.js` — users and sessions use SQLite
   - `services/imageHash.js` — image hash library uses SQLite
   - `services/serpReport.js` — SERP reports use SQLite
   - `routes/skuRoutes.js` — SKUs use SQLite (no more per-brand JSON files)

3. **Same API signatures preserved** — all routes work unchanged

4. **Dockerfile updated** — added `python3 make g++` for native `better-sqlite3` compilation

5. **Tested:** Server startup, user registration, login, brand CRUD, listing queries, stats, report history, subscription — all verified working
